"During rehabilitation, medical treatment is completed, and patients are brought back to a satisfactory nutritional status. In the case of kwashiorkor, the disappearance of oedema terminates initial treatment; if oedema does not disappear within one week however, the diet should nevertheless be more concentrated than during initial treatment -failing that, malnutrition of a kwashiorkor-marasmus type can develop. # The nutritional aspects of rehabilitation\nDuring nutritional rehabilitation, the amount of food should cover maintenance and nutritional catch-up requirements."